      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;squid-proxy-is-a-great-tool-that-allows-us-to-do-multiple-things-one-of-them-is-to-function-as-a-forward-proxy-and-with-the-use-of-acls-we-can-filter-sites-using-the-sni&#34;&gt;Squid Proxy is a great tool that allows us to do multiple things; one of them is to function as a forward proxy, and with the use of ACLs, we can filter sites using the SNI.&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;installation&#34;&gt;installation&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Squid proxy is installed via apt-get. The squid-openssl version is of interest to us since it contains ssl-bump. If our distribution does not include squid-openssl, it must be installed manually.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo apt-get install squid-openssl&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://pacodiazdg.github.io/images/9034cefa695d9cf73265449df6f2ba05025a2268660c542a44fb1107d1ef4b2610cde1591a62ded00bde3f9d8d2aa3d307087828e21ae3a8b9cfe05567708983.png&#34; alt=&#34;Name&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
